history.content:
Since you're going into Robotics, having a good background in data/ML will be key. Here are some foundational classes that will help:

Math 110: Light math class that goes over foundational linear algebra topics.

EECS 127: A must-take for anyone working in anything remotely related to ML/Optimization.

Data 100: Light math/programming class to teach applied fundamentals of data science.

children.subject: op here. Thanks for the input! I think I'm going to first try to enroll in 70, 120, and 106a (because 61c class times are still tba :c) and then pick which one I ultimately want to keep

If you're interested in the controls side of robotics, 120 / 128 is a requirement. Also, 106A is a reasonably light course and shows you robotics applications, so you can decide if you want to do robotics.

history.content:
I am a cs-intended freshman who will have completed CS61A/B and EE16A/B by the end of this semester, with pretty decent grades. I can't say that my plans will never change, but I am really interested in getting into robotics.

For next semester, I am planning to take CS70 and CS61C. I would love to take another technical class to gain background for more major-related classes in the future. However, the HKN course guide shows that most upperdiv CS courses require CS70 and most of the next EE courses go into devices, which I am not too interested in.

EE120 looks good, but it seems like the seats are filling up quickly. And I remember Physics 7B filled up really quickly last semester as well. 

Are there any other technical classes I can take alongside CS70 and CS61C?
history.subject: Technical classes to take with CS70 and CS61C
